                    </dt>
                    <dd class="accordion-content accordionItem is-collapsed" id="accordion1" aria-hidden="true">
                        <p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>Wash Hands Thoroughly:</b><br>
                                Wash your hands with soap and warm water for at least 20 seconds before handling food, after
                                touching raw meat or eggs, and after using the restroom.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Clean Surfaces Regularly:</b><br>
                                Wipe down countertops, cutting boards, and utensils with hot, soapy water after each
                                use to prevent cross-contamination and the spread of bacteria.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Separate Raw and Cooked Foods:</b><br>
                                Use separate cutting boards and utensils for raw meats and ready-to-eat foods to avoid cross-contamination. Store them separately in the fridge.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Cook Foods to Safe Temperatures:</b><br>
                                Use a food thermometer to ensure that meat, poultry, seafood, and eggs are cooked to their safe internal temperatures to kill harmful bacteria.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Properly Store Food:</b><br>
                                Refrigerate perishable foods promptly and store raw meats on the bottom shelf to prevent drips onto other foods. Use airtight containers for leftovers.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Regularly Change Dishcloths and Sponges:</b><br>
                                Replace dishcloths and sponges frequently, ideally daily, or sanitize them by microwaving damp sponges for 1-2 minutes to kill bacteria.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Keep Refrigerator Clean:</b><br>
                                Clean spills immediately and regularly remove expired or spoiled foods to maintain a clean and safe refrigerator environment.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Use Clean Kitchen Towels:</b><br>
                                Use clean kitchen towels to dry hands and wipe surfaces. Launder them frequently in hot water to eliminate bacteria.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Avoid Eating Raw Batter or Dough:</b><br>
                                Refrain from consuming raw batter or dough containing raw eggs or flour to prevent the risk of foodborne illnesses.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Practice Good Personal Hygiene:</b><br>
                                Tie back long hair, avoid touching your face, and wear clean clothes while cooking to minimize the risk of contamination.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        </p>
